<i>Are you kidding me?</i>

00:17:34.219 --> 00:17:35.621 line:95%,end
No, I don't have an Afro.

00:17:36.021 --> 00:17:39.091 line:95%,end
<i>That's not the black experience</i>
<i>that we know.</i>

00:17:39.158 --> 00:17:41.727 line:95%,end
And there's nothing wrong with LaQuifa--

00:17:41.794 --> 00:17:43.295 line:95%,end
the LaQuifas of the world.

00:17:43.362 --> 00:17:45.297 line:95%,end
<i>But that's not Nia's experience.</i>

00:17:45.364 --> 00:17:46.498 line:95%,end
<i>It is not my experience.</i>

00:17:46.565 --> 00:17:48.200 line:95%,end
My name is Holly.

00:17:48.267 --> 00:17:51.236 line:95%,end
I'm as far away from LaQuifa
as you can get.

00:17:51.303 --> 00:17:54.573 line:95%,end
That is not who I am
and that is not who Nia is.

00:17:56.508 --> 00:17:57.476 line:95%,end
ABBY: Turn around.

00:17:58.043 --> 00:18:00.679 line:95%,end
<i>Holly wants her daughter</i>
<i>to be like every other little girl.</i>

00:18:00.746 --> 00:18:03.582 line:5%,start
Nia has an advantage over everybody else.

00:18:03.649 --> 00:18:06.085 line:5%,start
She can play many different ethnicities.

00:18:06.151 --> 00:18:10.155 line:95%,end
And it's my job to make her
capitalize those opportunities.

00:18:10.222 --> 00:18:11.857 line:95%,end
<i>Different is good.</i>

00:18:11.924 --> 00:18:15.027 line:95%,end
<i>She has what it takes,</i>
<i>and yet her mom wants her</i>

00:18:15.094 --> 00:18:17.663 line:95%,end
<i>to be like Paige, and Maddie, and Chloe.</i>

00:18:17.729 --> 00:18:19.098 line:95%,end
This is show business.

00:18:19.164 --> 00:18:21.133 line:95%,end
When they're looking
for somebody different,

00:18:21.200 --> 00:18:22.401 line:95%,end
they're going to love Nia.

00:18:23.168 --> 00:18:24.770 line:95%,end
I think these could go a little higher.


00:18:27.339 --> 00:18:30.042 line:95%,end
(dramatic music playing)

00:18:33.145 --> 00:18:34.713 line:5%,start
I can't take all the late night.

00:18:38.117 --> 00:18:39.218 line:5%,start
I never drink.

00:18:39.284 --> 00:18:41.153 line:5%,start
But after having to buy an Afro

00:18:41.220 --> 00:18:43.122 line:95%,end
<i>and seeing that Leopard costume,</i>

00:18:43.188 --> 00:18:44.890 line:95%,end
I about had it.

00:18:44.957 --> 00:18:48.327 line:95%,end
What I took objection to was
just about the whole LaQuifa number.

00:18:48.393 --> 00:18:51.463 line:95%,end
I never have denied my Black heritage.
I'm very proud of it.

00:18:51.530 --> 00:18:53.332 line:95%,end
But it has to--I don't want
to be a stereotypical

00:18:53.398 --> 00:18:55.100 line:95%,end
-from the '70s wearing an Afro.
-And I agree with that.

00:18:55.167 --> 00:18:56.869 line:95%,end
We're in the 21st century.

00:18:56.935 --> 00:18:59.271 line:5%,start
KELLY: I think Holly's
being a little overdramatic.

00:18:59.338 --> 00:19:01.206 line:5%,start
Her daughter's wearing an Afro wig.

00:19:01.273 --> 00:19:02.407 line:95%,end
<i>What's the big deal?</i>

00:19:02.474 --> 00:19:03.909 line:95%,end
She's going to have her picking cotton.

00:19:03.976 --> 00:19:07.079 line:95%,end
Might as well, or a scarf on her head
and being Aunt Jemima.

00:19:07.146 --> 00:19:09.448 line:95%,end
-I don't want that.
-Did you just say picking cotton?

00:19:09.515 --> 00:19:10.749 line:95%,end
-HOLLY: Well, that's what it's like.
-(laughter)

00:19:10.816 --> 00:19:11.783 line:95%,end
It's the same type of thing.

00:19:11.850 --> 00:19:13.118 line:95%,end
Swing low sweet chariot,

00:19:13.185 --> 00:19:14.620 line:95%,end
and just let's pick some cotton
or something.

00:19:14.686 --> 00:19:16.088 line:95%,end
-KELLY: It doesn't--like--
-We have worked so hard

00:19:16.155 --> 00:19:17.723 line:95%,end
-to get beyond that.
-KELLY: I agree with you.

00:19:17.789 --> 00:19:19.625 line:95%,end
HOLLY: <i>For me, it's very political.</i>

00:19:19.691 --> 00:19:22.361 line:5%,start
Politics is all about who has to power
and who has the control.

00:19:22.427 --> 00:19:24.463 line:95%,end
<i>I don't have the power</i>
<i>to choose Nia's music.</i>

00:19:24.530 --> 00:19:25.764 line:95%,end
<i>Abby gets to choose that.</i>

00:19:25.831 --> 00:19:28.500 line:95%,end
And Abby has the control
and the power in depicting

00:19:28.567 --> 00:19:30.035 line:95%,end
how she wants Nia portrayed.

00:19:30.102 --> 00:19:32.371 line:95%,end
I'm definitely frustrated.
I'm at the end of my rope.

00:19:32.437 --> 00:19:35.340 line:95%,end
I don't know if I'm going to be able
to hang in there much longer.

00:19:37.743 --> 00:19:40.579 line:5%,start
(upbeat music playing)

00:19:40.646 --> 00:19:42.414 line:5%,start
(indistinct chatter)

00:19:45.250 --> 00:19:48.086 line:95%,end
ABBY: Bus driver,
how come you came this way?

00:19:48.153 --> 00:19:49.955 line:95%,end
You're throwing everybody
around back here.

00:19:50.022 --> 00:19:53.692 line:5%,start
We're heading to the Starpower
competition in Connecticut.

00:19:53.759 --> 00:19:55.494 line:5%,start
And this is going to be tough.

00:19:55.561 --> 00:19:59.198 line:95%,end
<i>The judges are going</i>
<i>to be looking for technique, of course,</i>

00:19:59.264 --> 00:20:03.168 line:95%,end
showmanship, costuming, and passion.

00:20:03.235 --> 00:20:05.070 line:95%,end
So when the dancers step out there,

00:20:05.137 --> 00:20:08.240 line:95%,end
they're truly passionate about their craft
and what they're doing.

00:20:08.674 --> 00:20:10.108 line:95%,end
Mackenzie!

00:20:10.175 --> 00:20:11.143 line:95%,end
Here!

00:20:11.210 --> 00:20:13.245 line:95%,end
-Maddie!
-Here!

00:20:13.946 --> 00:20:15.080 line:95%,end
ABBY: <i>Cathy is too good for us.</i>

00:20:15.581 --> 00:20:18.483 line:95%,end
<i>She gets to ride in the Mercedes</i>
<i>while we're on the bus?</i>

00:20:18.550 --> 00:20:20.185 line:95%,end
<i>Who does she think she is?</i>

00:20:20.252 --> 00:20:21.954 line:95%,end
<i>We all know it's a C Class.</i>

00:20:23.889 --> 00:20:25.724 line:95%,end
(upbeat music playing)

00:20:25.791 --> 00:20:28.493 line:95%,end
The woman at the wig shop
thought I was crazy,

00:20:28.560 --> 00:20:31.096 line:95%,end
getting an Afro for 10-year-old girl.

00:20:31.163 --> 00:20:32.664 line:95%,end
Oh, you ended up getting one?

00:20:32.731 --> 00:20:34.499 line:95%,end
-I found one.
-CHRISTI: Is it blonde?

00:20:34.566 --> 00:20:36.201 line:95%,end
(laughter)

00:20:36.268 --> 00:20:37.469 line:95%,end
HOLLY: That would have been--
that would have been good.

00:20:37.536 --> 00:20:40.005 line:95%,end
<i>There are lots of wigs</i>
<i>I would like to choose from for Nia.</i>

00:20:40.072 --> 00:20:42.207 line:95%,end
<i>I would never select an Afro wig.</i>

00:20:42.274 --> 00:20:45.377 line:5%,start
I would like for Nia to be beautiful

00:20:45.444 --> 00:20:46.745 line:95%,end
and not stereotyped

00:20:46.812 --> 00:20:49.581 line:95%,end
as someone with an Afro from the '70s.

00:20:49.648 --> 00:20:52.751 line:95%,end
(upbeat music playing)

00:20:58.423 --> 00:21:01.426 line:95%,end
(laughter)

00:21:05.364 --> 00:21:07.065 line:95%,end
I thought you liked Gummy Worms!

00:21:07.132 --> 00:21:08.734 line:95%,end
(laughter)

00:21:10.369 --> 00:21:12.904 line:95%,end
Getting sleep on a bus
with a bunch of kids

00:21:12.971 --> 00:21:14.039 line:95%,end
just doesn't work.

00:21:16.541 --> 00:21:19.278 line:5%,start
(upbeat music playing)

00:21:19.344 --> 00:21:22.014 line:95%,end
(cheering and applause)

00:21:22.080 --> 00:21:23.515 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: <i>So here we are at Starpower,</i>

00:21:23.582 --> 00:21:25.384 line:5%,start
and this is the big competition for us.

00:21:25.450 --> 00:21:27.319 line:5%,start
Our girls need to do really well.

00:21:27.386 --> 00:21:30.389 line:95%,end
(upbeat music playing)

00:21:31.890 --> 00:21:34.760 line:5%,start
ABBY: Moms, they're running
